Build a complete Event-Driven Microservices platform called "DevFlow"
with the following exact specifications:

TECH STACK:
- 4 FastAPI microservices (User, Order, Notification, Analytics)
- Redis Pub/Sub as message broker
- PostgreSQL (one database per service, separate containers)
- Nginx as API Gateway / reverse proxy
- React + Vite frontend with Tailwind CSS
- WebSocket for real-time event streaming to dashboard
- Docker Compose orchestrating everything

MICROSERVICES:

1. User Service (port 8001)
   - POST /users → create user → publish "user.created" event
   - GET /users → list users
   - GET /users/{id} → get user
   - Own PostgreSQL database: users_db

2. Order Service (port 8002)
   - POST /orders → create order → publish "order.created" event
   - GET /orders → list orders
   - Subscribes to "user.created" (logs when new user can place orders)
   - Own PostgreSQL database: orders_db

3. Notification Service (port 8003)
   - Subscribes to "user.created" → sends welcome notification
   - Subscribes to "order.created" → sends order confirmation
   - GET /notifications → list all notifications sent
   - Stores notifications in its own PostgreSQL database: notifications_db

4. Analytics Service (port 8004)
   - Subscribes to ALL events
   - Tracks: total users, total orders, events per minute
   - GET /analytics/summary → returns aggregated stats
   - Own PostgreSQL database: analytics_db

NGINX (port 80):
  /api/users → User Service
  /api/orders → Order Service
  /api/notifications → Notification Service
  /api/analytics → Analytics Service
  / → React Frontend

REACT DASHBOARD (port 3000):
Pages:
