Create a reusable circuit breaker utility used by 
services that call other services.

FILE: services/shared/circuit_breaker.py

Implement a CircuitBreaker class with these exact states:
  CLOSED (normal — requests pass through)
  OPEN (failing — requests blocked, return fallback)
  HALF_OPEN (testing — one request allowed through)

Class definition:
class CircuitBreaker:
    def __init__(
        self,
        name: str,
        failure_threshold: int = 5,
        recovery_timeout: int = 30,
        expected_exception: type = Exception
    )
    
    async def call(self, func, *args, **kwargs):
        # If OPEN and timeout not passed: raise CircuitBreakerOpen
        # If OPEN and timeout passed: switch to HALF_OPEN, try call
        # If HALF_OPEN and call succeeds: switch to CLOSED
        # If HALF_OPEN and call fails: switch back to OPEN
        # If CLOSED and call fails: increment failure count
        # If failure count >= threshold: switch to OPEN
        # If CLOSED and call succeeds: reset failure count

    def get_state(self) -> dict:
        returns: name, state, failure_count, 
                 last_failure_time, next_retry_time

